   M http://src.chromium.org/viewvc/native_client/trunk/src/native_client/tests/debug_stub/debugger_test.c?r1=9696&amp;r2=9695&amp;pathrev=9696
   M http://src.chromium.org/viewvc/native_client/trunk/src/native_client/tests/debug_stub/debug_stub_test.py?r1=9696&amp;r2=9695&amp;pathrev=9696

Debug stub tests: Remove one use of the x86 int3 instruction

This is in preparation for enabling all of the debug stub tests on Mac
OS X, where a kernel bug prevents us from using int3.

We change the debug stub's thread suspension tests to use 'hlt'
instead.  They must now handle SIGSEGV as well as SIGTRAP.

